'''George Hogben''' [[Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]] (14 July 1853 – 26 April 1920) was a New Zealand educationalist and seismologist. He was born in [[Islington]], [[Middlesex]], [[England]] on 14 July 1853, and died after a short illness at home in [[Khandallah]], [[Wellington]] .<ref name="DNZB Hogben">{{DNZB|title=George Hogben|first= Herbert|last= Roth|id=2h44|accessdate=23 April 2017}}</ref> He was Inspector-General of Schools in New Zealand and was appointed CMG in the [[1915 New Year Honours]].

