The '''Wiley Bad Science Series''' is a series of books by [[John Wiley & Sons Publishing]] about [[scientific misconceptions]].
The ''[[Publishers Weekly]]'' review of the first book in the series, ''Bad Astronomy'', mentioned that the subsequent books will be about scientific misconceptions in biology, weather and the earth.<ref>[http://www.publishersweekly.com/978-0-471-40976-2 A review by ''Publishers Weekly'']</ref>
*2002: ''[[Bad Astronomy: Misconceptions and Misuses Revealed, from Astrology to the Moon Landing "Hoax"]]'', by [[Philip C. Plait]] <ref name=ba_ba>[http://www.barnesandnoble.com/w/bad-astronomy-philip-c-plait/1111794712?ean=9780471409762 ''Bad Astronomy'' at Barnes & Noble]</ref> * 2003: ''[[Bad Medicine (Wanjek)|Bad Medicine: Misconceptions and Misuses Revealed, from Distance Healing to Vitamin O]]'', by [[Christopher Wanjek]] <ref name=ba_bm>[http://www.barnesandnoble.com/w/bad-medicine-christopher-wanjek/1111765037?ean=9780471434993 ''Bad Medicine'' at Barnes & Noble]</ref>
